title: Members appointed to assess financial assistance for fallen heroes
content_text: The Government announced today (February 15) the appointment of four members to the Committee on Financial Assistance for Family Members of those who Sacrifice their Lives to Save Others. The Committee is chaired by the Secretary for Health and Welfare. The four members appointed are the Hon Bernard Charnwut Chan, Mr Chau How Chen, Ms Lam Shuk Yee, and Mrs Leung Ngai Mou Yin, Justina. They are appointed for a term of three years with effect from February 11, 2002. Secretary

on January 9 this year. Family members of an individual lawfully residing
in Hong Kong, who dies as a result of trying to save or protect another
person in Hong Kong, are eligible to apply for financial assistance. The
